Casals - A Portrait for Radio: ALBERT KAHN: Periodically and, strangely enough, not infrequently - I meet someone who has never heard of the name of Pablo Casals before
Casals - A Portrait for Radio: KAHN: Not so very long ago - when I was in Puerto Rico last - we were talking about how we happened to come together originally
Casals - A Portrait for Radio: KAHN: It's a very strange feeling - when you're sitting, talking to Don Pablo - to realize that you're speaking with a man who played...
Casals - A Portrait for Radio: KAHN: You have to understand that I am speaking not as a musicologist - music is not primarily my field
Casals - A Portrait for Radio: KAHN: In the United States today, I suppose his name is most closely associated with his yearly appearances at the Marlboro Festival
Casals - A Portrait for Radio: PABLO CASALS: Now I say that the Marlboro School is the best possible - the best school in the world
Casals - A Portrait for Radio: KAHN: One question that was recently asked me regarding Casals, I found of special interest
Casals - A Portrait for Radio: FELIX GALAMIR: May I inject myself, my own personality into this discussion for a moment?
Casals - A Portrait for Radio: GUILLERMO FIGUEROA: Last year in the festival we had played a Bruckner symphony
Casals - A Portrait for Radio: KAHN: And there's one rather interesting contradiction that is perhaps worth mentioning
Casals - A Portrait for Radio: GALAMIR: Now Casals is a very strong personality
Casals - A Portrait for Radio: KAHN: It was Sir Francis Bacon who said that there is no beauty which hath not some imperfection in its being
Casals - A Portrait for Radio: GALAMIR: I also think that basically Casals is a very simple person

Stokowski - A Portrait for Radio: STOKOWSKI: First of all, it's our privilege and our necessity to try to realize what was in the soul of the composer...

Stokowski - A Portrait for Radio: STOKOWSKI: I find that every day come new possibilities and new ideas and they must not be ignored
